Condition : 6 - Prior to the relevant works details in the form of a statement of all proposed repairs, alterations and retentions for each room in the historic buildings and internal elevations showing the proposed changes shall be submitted to the local planning authority for approval in writing. The details shall include:
- Details of all proposed internal joinery and mouldings at a scale of 1:5 for mouldings and 1:20 for joinery;
- Window schedule itemising windows to be replaced with justification for their replacement and proposed design;
- Details of ceilings if there are replacements proposed. These should be of traditional timber lath and plaster construction or to match the existing;
- Details of service runs. These should be concealed and when the historic fabric would have to be removed it should be made good / replaced using like for like materials and techniques to best conservation practice. Existing appropriate service ducts should be re-used;
- Pointing schedule. All repointing should be done in lime to an appropriate historic appearance.

The works shall be implemented in accordance with the approved details.
